nmos.tech
  Technology file for magic (VLSI CAD tool).  Place in /usr/lib/magic/sys or /usr/lib64/magic/sys.
  Obtained from an old Magic version 6 distribution:
    http://embedded.eecs.berkeley.edu/pubs/downloads/magic/magic_6.tar.Z
  linked from
    http://embedded.eecs.berkeley.edu/pubs/downloads/magic/

klayout-nmos.lyp
  Layer properties (colors and transparency) for klayout.  Specified Mead-and-Conway-like colors
  for NMOS GDSII files.  To load this file automatically, see
    http://klayout.de/forum/comments.php?DiscussionID=102&page=1#Item_0
  Other helpful settings for klayout:
    In File->Setup:
      Application->Layer List:  use klayout-nmos.lyp as default layer table
      Display->General:  use 2x oversampling for a nicer display
      Navigation->New Cell:  check "Select all hierarchy levels"
